  "commentary": "With SPX at 6597.39 sitting between the max negative gamma at 6590 (-8849.4M) and max positive gamma at 6605 (+14782.1M), dealers are likely covering short hedges as spot bounces off the amplifying 6590 level but will start selling delta into any push toward the massive +14782.1M wall at 6605. The PIN regime with 8564.1M total GEX suggests strong mean-reverting forces, keeping price action contained within this tight 6590-6605 range where dealers flip from buying to selling. Key inflection points are 6590 breakdown (dealer selling accelerates) versus 6605 breakthrough (removes major supply wall toward 6610's +10430.6M barrier).\n\nBottom line: expect choppy action pinned between 6590-6605 with dealers providing liquidity at both ends.",
